==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Poesy
<hw>Po"e*sy</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[F.
<ets>po⟦eacute⟧sie</ets> (cf. It. <ets>poesia</ets>), L.
<ets>poesis</ets>, from Gr. <?/. from <?/ to make. Cf.
<er>Posy</er>.]</ety>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>1.</sn> <def>The art of composing poems; poetical skill or
faculty; <as>as, the heavenly gift of <ex>poesy</ex></as>.</def>
<rj><au>Shak.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Poetry; metrical composition; poems.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Music and <qex>poesy</qex> used to quicken you.</q>
<rj><qau>Shak.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <def>A short conceit or motto engraved on a ring or other
thing; a posy.</def> <rj><au>Bacon.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Poet</ent>⟦br⟧
